### `src/components/ui/ScrollSpy/ScrollSpy.module.scss` — final changes

```scss
// Replace the comment block + .highlightLabelAnchor rule:

// Portaled label for the currently-active (or drag-targeted) notch.
// Rendered as a direct child of <body> so mix-blend-mode: difference blends
// against the page content below rather than being isolated by the rail's
// fixed-position stacking context. Color: #fff + difference yields automatic
// inverse-of-backdrop contrast — black text on light backgrounds, white text
// on dark backgrounds, without pixel sampling or per-section annotation.
//
// Positioning split across two elements so framer-motion's `x` animation
// on the inner span does not overwrite the anchor's placement (AP-070).
// Anchor is `position: fixed` with `right` driven by JS:
//   right = window.innerWidth − notch.left + 8px
// This places the label's right edge 8px left of the notch's left edge —
// identical to `.label { right: calc(100% + var(--portfolio-spacer-1x)) }`.
// The previous approach used `left: notch.left` + `transform: translate(-100% - 1x, …)`,
// which relied on `-100%` resolving against the element's own shrink-to-fit width.
// That resolution is unstable when `will-change` promotes the element to a compositor
// layer before the CSS class is fully applied — causing the label to land at `left: notch.left`
// (rightward of the rail, clipping past the viewport). Switching to `right` eliminates
// the reference-box dependency entirely. Only `translateY(-50%)` is retained for vertical
// centering — its reference axis (element height) is stable at paint time. (FB-156 iter 2)
//
// `mix-blend-mode` must sit on the element whose PARENT is the root stacking
// context (i.e. <body>) — that's the anchor, not the inner span. The span
// is inside the anchor's stacking context (created by `position: fixed` +
// `transform`), so putting the blend mode on the span would isolate it to
// the anchor's empty interior and produce no inversion. Direct recurrence
// of AP-069 within FB-156's refactor. See FB-156 iteration 3.
.highlightLabelAnchor {
  position: fixed;
  transform: translateY(-50%);  // vertical centering only; horizontal handled by `right` (JS-driven)
  color: #fff;
  mix-blend-mode: difference;
  z-index: var(--portfolio-z-scrollspy);
  pointer-events: none;
  will-change: top, right;
}
```

